<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="521" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Smith</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams–Extracts.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Because of seriousness of revolution in north, President Zamor will go to
                            the front tomorrow.* * * In the absence of the President the Government
                            will be in the hands of a Commission to be created tonight and which
                            will act in conjunction with the Cabinet. Port au Prince is quiet but
                            the presence of a naval vessel appears to be of the utmost
                            importance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>